      • setTimestamp

        public T setTimestamp​(long timestamp)
        Sets an explicit timestamp. The instant the timestamp describes must be measured in milliseconds since the epoch. Not setting this means a timestamp set to "now" will be generated on send().
        Parameters:
        timestamp - to set (millis since the epoch).
        Returns:
